<title>JAPAN: Daihyaku Mutual reveals problem loans.</title>
<headline>Daihyaku Mutual reveals problem loans.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1996-11-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Daihyaku Mutual Life Insurance Co has disclosed its restructured loans (in billions of yen unless specified):</p>
<p>					end-Sep 96     end-Mar 96</p>
<p>  Restructured loans	    18.02	    69.21</p>
<p>  Bad loans			 32.16	     4.48</p>
<p>  Non-performing loans	  32.73	    16.31</p>
<p>  Total problem loans	   82.92	     90.0</p>
<p>Restructured loans are those on which interest rates have been cut to help corporate restructuring. Bad loans are to bankrupt firms and non-performing are those with interest payments in arrears by six months or more.</p>
</text>
